OL,3,CChoosing a new pope: How the Vatican
OL,4,Cturns its smoke signals black or white
OL,6,FThe colour of the smoke tells the
OL,7,Fstory: black means no cardinal has
OL,8,Fsecured the required two-thirds
OL,9,Fmajority, while white signals that the
OL,10,Fcardinals have reached a consensus and
OL,11,Felected a new pope.
OL,13,FThe tradition of using smoke dates
OL,14,Fback to the 1800s, but the first
OL,15,Frecorded use of white and black smoke
OL,16,Fto mark the result was at the 1903
OL,17,FConclave.
OL,19,FHow is the smoke created?
