OL,3,CChoosing a new pope: How the Vatican
OL,4,Cturns its smoke signals black or white
OL,6,FInside the Sistine Chapel, two stoves
OL,7,Fare temporarily set up for the
OL,8,Fconclave, both connected to a flue - a
OL,9,Fpipe within a chimney - that leads the
OL,10,Fsmoke up through the chapel roof and
OL,11,Foutside.
OL,13,FThe left stove is used to burn the
OL,14,Fballots, while the other stove creates
OL,15,Fthe smoke's colour.
OL,17,FWhat gives the smoke its distinctive
OL,18,Fblack or white colour?
