OL,3,CChoosing a new pope: How the Vatican
OL,4,Cturns its smoke signals black or white
OL,6,FTo create the different colours of
OL,7,Fsmoke, specific chemicals are added
OL,8,Fduring the burning process.
OL,10,FAfter each voting session, chemicals
OL,11,Fare burned in the right stove to
OL,12,Fproduce either a black or white colour
OL,13,Ffor the smoke that is created in the
OL,14,Fleft stove, where the ballots are
OL,15,Fburned.
OL,17,FFor black smoke, a chemical compound
OL,18,Fof potassium perchlorate, anthracene,
OL,19,Fand sulfur is used to make the smoke
OL,20,Fdarker.
